1 (III) Is a candidate for a kidney transplant; and
2 (e) Any follow-up services that are included within a payment
3 for a service described in paragraphs (a) to (d), inclusive.
4 2. The Director shall not include under Medicaid coverage
5 pursuant to this section for any care or service not described in
6 subsection 1, including, without limitation:
7 (a) Elective surgery;
8 (b) Prescription drugs, unless dispensed or administered by a
9 provider of health care as part of the care or treatment described
10 in subsection 1;
11 (c) Preventive care;
12 (d) Rehabilitative services;
13 (e) Personal care services;
14 (f) Physical, occupational or speech therapy;
15 (g) Case management services;
16 (h) Prosthetics, orthotics, durable medical equipment or
17 medical supplies;
18 (i) Dental services;
19 (j) Hospice care;
20 (k) Treatment for substance use disorder;
21 (l) Services for routine prenatal care;
22 (m) Except as otherwise provided by subparagraph (4) of
23 paragraph (d) of subsection 1, organ transplants and stem cell
24 transplants; and
25 (n) Except as otherwise provided by subparagraph (1) of
26 paragraph (d) of subsection 1, continuing care, including, without
27 limitation, care and services provided by a facility for the
28 dependent.
29 3. The Department may not provide coverage under Medicaid
30 pursuant to this section for the care described in paragraph (d) of
31 subsection 1 unless the Department determines, before the care
32 being rendered, that such care is medically necessary and
33 appropriate, based on the condition of the person to whom the
34 care may be provided. To provide coverage for the care described
35 in subparagraph (1) of paragraph (d) of subsection 1, the
36 Department must additionally determine that the care is necessary
37 to prevent the condition of the person from rapidly becoming an
38 emergency medical condition.
39 4. The Department shall:
40 (a) Apply for any waiver of federal law or apply for any
41 amendment to the State Plan for Medicaid that is necessary to
42 obtain federal financial participation to pay for the cost of
43 coverage provided under this section.
44 (b) Fully cooperate in good faith with the Federal Government
45 during the application process to satisfy the requirements of the
