5 5. As used in this section:
6 (a) “Emergency medical condition” has the meaning ascribed
7 to it in 42 U.S.C. § 1396b(v)(3).
8 (b) “Emergency medical transportation services” means
9 emergency medical transportation services provided by an
10 ambulance, air ambulance or vehicle of a fire-fighting agency,
11 including, without limitation, services provided by emergency
12 medical technicians, advanced emergency medical technicians
13 and paramedics in prestabilizing patients and preparing patients
14 for transport.
15 (c) “Facility for skilled nursing” has the meaning ascribed to
16 it in NRS 449.0039.
17 (d) “Facility for the dependent” has the meaning ascribed to it
18 in NRS 449.0045.
19 (e) “Facility for the treatment of irreversible renal disease”
20 has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 449.0046.
21 (f) “Independent center for emergency medical care” has the
22 meaning ascribed to it in NRS 449.013.
23 (g) “Medically necessary” means health care services or
24 products that a prudent physician would provide to a patient to
25 prevent, diagnose or treat an illness, injury or disease or any
26 symptom thereof, that are necessary and which are:
27 (1) Provided in accordance with generally accepted
28 standards of medical practice;
29 (2) Clinically appropriate for the type, frequency, extent,
30 location and duration;
31 (3) Not primarily provided for the convenience of the
32 patient, physician or other provider of health care;
33 (4) Required to improve a specific health condition of the
34 patient or to preserve the existing state of health of the patient;
35 and
36 (5) The most clinically appropriate level of health care that
37 may be safely provided to the patient.
38 (h) “Provider of health care” has the meaning ascribed to it in
39 NRS 629.031.
